{
  "video_id": "2cU56SWXHFw",
  "title": "James Geary, metaphorically speaking",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 15260.0,
      "end_time": 19260.0,
      "text": "Metaphor lives a secret life all around us."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 19260.0,
      "end_time": 23260.0,
      "text": "We utter about six metaphors a minute."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 23260.0,
      "end_time": 25260.0,
      "text": "Metaphorical thinking is essential"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 25260.0,
      "end_time": 28260.0,
      "text": "to how we understand ourselves and others,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 28260.0,
      "end_time": 31260.0,
      "text": "how we communicate, learn, discover"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 31260.0,
      "end_time": 33260.0,
      "text": "and invent."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 33260.0,
      "end_time": 38260.0,
      "text": "But metaphor is a way of thought before it is a way with words."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 38260.0,
      "end_time": 41260.0,
      "text": "Now, to assist me in explaining this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 41260.0,
      "end_time": 44260.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve enlisted the help of one of our greatest philosophers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 44260.0,
      "end_time": 48260.0,
      "text": "the reigning king of the metaphorians,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 48260.0,
      "end_time": 50260.0,
      "text": "a man whose contributions to the field"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 50260.0,
      "end_time": 53260.0,
      "text": "are so great that he himself"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 53260.0,
      "end_time": 55260.0,
      "text": "has become a metaphor."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 55260.0,
      "end_time": 59260.0,
      "text": "I am, of course, referring to none other"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 59260.0,
      "end_time": 61260.0,
      "text": "than Elvis Presley."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 61260.0,
      "end_time": 62260.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 62260.0,
      "end_time": 65260.0,
      "text": "Now, &quot;All Shook Up&quot; is a great love song."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 65260.00000000001,
      "end_time": 67260.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s also a great example of how"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 67260.0,
      "end_time": 69260.0,
      "text": "whenever we deal with anything abstract --"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 69260.0,
      "end_time": 73260.0,
      "text": "ideas, emotions, feelings, concepts, thoughts --"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 73260.0,
      "end_time": 75260.0,
      "text": "we inevitably resort to metaphor."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 75260.0,
      "end_time": 80260.0,
      "text": "In &quot;All Shook Up,&quot; a touch is not a touch, but a chill."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 80260.0,
      "end_time": 83260.0,
      "text": "Lips are not lips, but volcanoes."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 83260.0,
      "end_time": 86260.0,
      "text": "She is not she, but a buttercup."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 86260.0,
      "end_time": 91260.0,
      "text": "And love is not love, but being all shook up."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 91260.0,
      "end_time": 95260.0,
      "text": "In this, Elvis is following Aristotle&#39;s classic definition of metaphor"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 95260.0,
      "end_time": 98260.0,
      "text": "as the process of giving the thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 98260.0,
      "end_time": 101260.0,
      "text": "a name that belongs to something else."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 101260.0,
      "end_time": 104260.0,
      "text": "This is the mathematics of metaphor."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 104260.0,
      "end_time": 106260.0,
      "text": "And fortunately it&#39;s very simple."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 106260.0,
      "end_time": 108260.0,
      "text": "X equals Y."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 108260.0,
      "end_time": 111260.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 111260.0,
      "end_time": 114260.0,
      "text": "This formula works wherever metaphor is present."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 114260.0,
      "end_time": 117260.0,
      "text": "Elvis uses it, but so does Shakespeare"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 117260.0,
      "end_time": 119260.0,
      "text": "in this famous line from &quot;Romeo and Juliet:&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 119260.0,
      "end_time": 122260.0,
      "text": "Juliet is the sun."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 122260.0,
      "end_time": 126260.0,
      "text": "Now, here, Shakespeare gives the thing, Juliet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 126260.0,
      "end_time": 131260.0,
      "text": "a name that belongs to something else, the sun."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 131260.0,
      "end_time": 134260.0,
      "text": "But whenever we give a thing a name that belongs to something else,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 134260.0,
      "end_time": 137260.0,
      "text": "we give it a whole network of analogies too."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 137260.0,
      "end_time": 140260.0,
      "text": "We mix and match what we know about the metaphor&#39;s source,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 140260.0,
      "end_time": 142260.0,
      "text": "in this case the sun,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 142260.0,
      "end_time": 145260.0,
      "text": "with what we know about its target, Juliet."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 145260.0,
      "end_time": 148260.0,
      "text": "And metaphor gives us a much more vivid understanding of Juliet"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 148260.0,
      "end_time": 153260.0,
      "text": "than if Shakespeare had literally described what she looks like."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 153260.0,
      "end_time": 155260.0,
      "text": "So, how do we make and understand metaphors?"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 155260.0,
      "end_time": 157260.0,
      "text": "This might look familiar."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 157260.0,
      "end_time": 159260.0,
      "text": "The first step is pattern recognition."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 159260.0,
      "end_time": 162260.0,
      "text": "Look at this image. What do you see?"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 162260.0,
      "end_time": 164260.0,
      "text": "Three wayward Pac-Men,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 164260.0,
      "end_time": 167260.0,
      "text": "and three pointy brackets are actually present."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 167260.0,
      "end_time": 169260.0,
      "text": "What we see, however,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 169260.0,
      "end_time": 171260.0,
      "text": "are two overlapping triangles."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 171260.0,
      "end_time": 174260.0,
      "text": "Metaphor is not just the detection of patterns;"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 174260.0,
      "end_time": 176260.0,
      "text": "it is the creation of patterns."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 176260.0,
      "end_time": 179260.0,
      "text": "Second step, conceptual synesthesia."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 179260.0,
      "end_time": 184260.0,
      "text": "Now, synesthesia is the experience of a stimulus in once sense organ"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 184260.0,
      "end_time": 186260.0,
      "text": "in another sense organ as well,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 186260.0,
      "end_time": 188260.0,
      "text": "such as colored hearing."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 188260.0,
      "end_time": 190260.0,
      "text": "People with colored hearing"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 190260.0,
      "end_time": 193260.0,
      "text": "actually see colors when they hear the sounds"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 193260.0,
      "end_time": 195260.0,
      "text": "of words or letters."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 195260.0,
      "end_time": 197260.0,
      "text": "We all have synesthetic abilities."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 197260.0,
      "end_time": 200260.0,
      "text": "This is the Bouba/Kiki test."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 200260.0,
      "end_time": 202260.0,
      "text": "What you have to do is identify which of these shapes"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 202260.0,
      "end_time": 206260.0,
      "text": "is called Bouba, and which is called Kiki."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 206260.0,
      "end_time": 207260.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 207260.0,
      "end_time": 209260.0,
      "text": "If you are like 98 percent of other people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 209260.0,
      "end_time": 213260.0,
      "text": "you will identify the round, amoeboid shape as Bouba,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 213260.0,
      "end_time": 216260.0,
      "text": "and the sharp, spiky one as Kiki."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 216260.0,
      "end_time": 218260.0,
      "text": "Can we do a quick show of hands?"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 218260.0,
      "end_time": 220260.0,
      "text": "Does that correspond?"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 220260.0,
      "end_time": 224260.0,
      "text": "Okay, I think 99.9 would about cover it."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 224260.0,
      "end_time": 226260.0,
      "text": "Why do we do that?"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 226260.0,
      "end_time": 230260.0,
      "text": "Because we instinctively find, or create,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 230260.0,
      "end_time": 232260.0,
      "text": "a pattern between the round shape"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 232260.0,
      "end_time": 235260.0,
      "text": "and the round sound of Bouba,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 235260.0,
      "end_time": 240260.0,
      "text": "and the spiky shape and the spiky sound of Kiki."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 240260.0,
      "end_time": 244260.0,
      "text": "And many of the metaphors we use everyday are synesthetic."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 244260.0,
      "end_time": 246260.0,
      "text": "Silence is sweet."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 246260.0,
      "end_time": 248260.0,
      "text": "Neckties are loud."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 248260.0,
      "end_time": 251260.0,
      "text": "Sexually attractive people are hot."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 251260.0,
      "end_time": 254260.0,
      "text": "Sexually unattractive people leave us cold."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 254260.0,
      "end_time": 257260.0,
      "text": "Metaphor creates a kind of conceptual synesthesia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 257260.0,
      "end_time": 259260.0,
      "text": "in which we understand one concept"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 259260.0,
      "end_time": 262260.0,
      "text": "in the context of another."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 262260.0,
      "end_time": 264260.0,
      "text": "Third step is cognitive dissonance."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 264260.0,
      "end_time": 266260.0,
      "text": "This is the Stroop test."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 266260.0,
      "end_time": 268260.0,
      "text": "What you need to do here is identify"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 268260.0,
      "end_time": 270260.0,
      "text": "as quickly as possible"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 270260.0,
      "end_time": 273260.0,
      "text": "the color of the ink in which these words are printed."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 273260.0,
      "end_time": 277260.0,
      "text": "You can take the test now."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 277260.0,
      "end_time": 279260.0,
      "text": "If you&#39;re like most people, you will experience"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 279260.0,
      "end_time": 281260.0,
      "text": "a moment of cognitive dissonance"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 281260.0,
      "end_time": 284260.0,
      "text": "when the name of the color"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 284260.0,
      "end_time": 286260.0,
      "text": "is printed in a differently colored ink."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 286260.0,
      "end_time": 289260.0,
      "text": "The test shows that we cannot ignore the literal meaning of words"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 289260.0,
      "end_time": 292260.0,
      "text": "even when the literal meaning gives the wrong answer."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 292260.0,
      "end_time": 294260.0,
      "text": "Stroop tests have been done with metaphor as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 294260.0,
      "end_time": 298260.0,
      "text": "The participants had to identify, as quickly as possible,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 298260.0,
      "end_time": 300260.0,
      "text": "the literally false sentences."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 300260.0,
      "end_time": 303260.0,
      "text": "They took longer to reject metaphors as false"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 303260.0,
      "end_time": 306260.0,
      "text": "than they did to reject literally false sentences."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 306260.0,
      "end_time": 309260.0,
      "text": "Why? Because we cannot ignore"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 309260.0,
      "end_time": 312260.0,
      "text": "the metaphorical meaning of words either."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 312260.0,
      "end_time": 315260.0,
      "text": "One of the sentences was, &quot;Some jobs are jails.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 315260.0,
      "end_time": 318260.0,
      "text": "Now, unless you&#39;re a prison guard,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 318260.0,
      "end_time": 321260.0,
      "text": "the sentence &quot;Some jobs are jails&quot; is literally false."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 321260.0,
      "end_time": 324260.0,
      "text": "Sadly, it&#39;s metaphorically true."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 324260.0,
      "end_time": 327260.0,
      "text": "And the metaphorical truth interferes with our ability"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 327260.0,
      "end_time": 329260.0,
      "text": "to identify it as literally false."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 329260.0,
      "end_time": 331260.0,
      "text": "Metaphor matters because"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 331260.0,
      "end_time": 334260.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s around us every day, all the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 334260.0,
      "end_time": 337260.0,
      "text": "Metaphor matters because it creates expectations."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 337260.0,
      "end_time": 341260.0,
      "text": "Pay careful attention the next time you read the financial news."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 341260.0,
      "end_time": 343260.0,
      "text": "Agent metaphors describe price movements"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 343260.0,
      "end_time": 345260.0,
      "text": "as the deliberate action of a living thing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 345260.0,
      "end_time": 349260.0,
      "text": "as in, &quot;The NASDAQ climbed higher.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 349260.0,
      "end_time": 352260.0,
      "text": "Object metaphors describe price movements"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 352260.0,
      "end_time": 354260.0,
      "text": "as non-living things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 354260.0,
      "end_time": 357260.0,
      "text": "as in, &quot;The Dow fell like a brick.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 357260.0,
      "end_time": 359260.0,
      "text": "Researchers asked a group of people"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 359260.0,
      "end_time": 361260.0,
      "text": "to read a clutch of market commentaries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 361260.0,
      "end_time": 364260.0,
      "text": "and then predict the next day&#39;s price trend."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 364260.0,
      "end_time": 366260.0,
      "text": "Those exposed to agent metaphors"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 366260.0,
      "end_time": 369260.0,
      "text": "had higher expectations that price trends would continue."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 369260.0,
      "end_time": 371260.0,
      "text": "And they had those expectations because"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 371260.0,
      "end_time": 374260.0,
      "text": "agent metaphors imply the deliberate action"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 374260.0,
      "end_time": 377260.0,
      "text": "of a living thing pursuing a goal."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 377260.0,
      "end_time": 379260.0,
      "text": "If, for example, house prices"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 379260.0,
      "end_time": 382260.0,
      "text": "are routinely described as climbing and climbing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 382260.0,
      "end_time": 384260.0,
      "text": "higher and higher, people might naturally assume"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 384260.0,
      "end_time": 386260.0,
      "text": "that that rise is unstoppable."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 386260.0,
      "end_time": 388260.0,
      "text": "They may feel confident, say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 388260.0,
      "end_time": 391260.0,
      "text": "in taking out mortgages they really can&#39;t afford."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 391260.0,
      "end_time": 394260.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s a hypothetical example of course."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 394260.0,
      "end_time": 398260.0,
      "text": "But this is how metaphor misleads."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 398260.0,
      "end_time": 401260.0,
      "text": "Metaphor also matters because it influences decisions"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 401260.0,
      "end_time": 404260.0,
      "text": "by activating analogies."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 404260.0,
      "end_time": 406260.0,
      "text": "A group of students was told that a small democratic country"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 406260.0,
      "end_time": 409260.0,
      "text": "had been invaded and had asked the U.S. for help."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 409260.0,
      "end_time": 411260.0,
      "text": "And they had to make a decision."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 411260.0,
      "end_time": 413260.0,
      "text": "What should they do?"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 413260.0,
      "end_time": 416260.0,
      "text": "Intervene, appeal to the U.N., or do nothing?"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 416260.0,
      "end_time": 418260.0,
      "text": "They were each then given one of three"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 418260.0,
      "end_time": 420260.0,
      "text": "descriptions of this hypothetical crisis."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 420260.0,
      "end_time": 423260.0,
      "text": "Each of which was designed to trigger"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 423260.0,
      "end_time": 425260.0,
      "text": "a different historical analogy:"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 425260.0,
      "end_time": 427260.0,
      "text": "World War II, Vietnam,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 427260.0,
      "end_time": 430260.0,
      "text": "and the third was historically neutral."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 430260.0,
      "end_time": 432260.0,
      "text": "Those exposed to the World War II scenario"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 432260.0,
      "end_time": 434260.0,
      "text": "made more interventionist recommendations"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 434260.0,
      "end_time": 436260.0,
      "text": "than the others."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 436260.0,
      "end_time": 439260.0,
      "text": "Just as we cannot ignore the literal meaning of words,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 439260.0,
      "end_time": 441260.0,
      "text": "we cannot ignore the analogies"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 441260.0,
      "end_time": 445260.0,
      "text": "that are triggered by metaphor."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 445260.0,
      "end_time": 448260.0,
      "text": "Metaphor matters because it opens the door to discovery."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 448260.0,
      "end_time": 451260.0,
      "text": "Whenever we solve a problem, or make a discovery,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 451260.0,
      "end_time": 454260.0,
      "text": "we compare what we know with what we don&#39;t know."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 454260.0,
      "end_time": 456260.0,
      "text": "And the only way to find out about the latter"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 456260.0,
      "end_time": 460260.0,
      "text": "is to investigate the ways it might be like the former."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 460260.0,
      "end_time": 464260.0,
      "text": "Einstein described his scientific method as combinatory play."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 464260.0,
      "end_time": 466260.0,
      "text": "He famously used thought experiments,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 466260.0,
      "end_time": 469260.0,
      "text": "which are essentially elaborate analogies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 469260.0,
      "end_time": 472260.0,
      "text": "to come up with some of his greatest discoveries."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 472260.0,
      "end_time": 474260.0,
      "text": "By bringing together what we know"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 474260.0,
      "end_time": 476260.0,
      "text": "and what we don&#39;t know through analogy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 476260.0,
      "end_time": 478260.0,
      "text": "metaphorical thinking strikes the spark"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 478260.0,
      "end_time": 482260.0,
      "text": "that ignites discovery."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 482260.0,
      "end_time": 486260.0,
      "text": "Now metaphor is ubiquitous, yet it&#39;s hidden."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 486260.0,
      "end_time": 489260.0,
      "text": "But you just have to look at the words around you"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 489260.0,
      "end_time": 491260.0,
      "text": "and you&#39;ll find it."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 491260.0,
      "end_time": 493260.0,
      "text": "Ralph Waldo Emerson described language"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 493260.0,
      "end_time": 495260.0,
      "text": "as &quot;fossil poetry.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 495260.0,
      "end_time": 497260.0,
      "text": "But before it was fossil poetry"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 497260.0,
      "end_time": 500260.0,
      "text": "language was fossil metaphor."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 500260.0,
      "end_time": 503260.0,
      "text": "And these fossils still breathe."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 503260.0,
      "end_time": 508260.0,
      "text": "Take the three most famous words in all of Western philosophy:"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 508260.0,
      "end_time": 510260.0,
      "text": "&quot;Cogito ergo sum.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 510260.0,
      "end_time": 514260.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s routinely translated as, &quot;I think, therefore I am.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 514260.0,
      "end_time": 516260.0,
      "text": "But there is a better translation."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 516260.0,
      "end_time": 518260.0,
      "text": "The Latin word &quot;cogito&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 518260.0,
      "end_time": 521260.0,
      "text": "is derived from the prefix &quot;co,&quot; meaning &quot;together,&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 521260.0,
      "end_time": 524260.0,
      "text": "and the verb &quot;agitare,&quot; meaning &quot;to shake.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 524260.0,
      "end_time": 527260.0,
      "text": "So, the original meaning of &quot;cogito&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 527260.0,
      "end_time": 529260.0,
      "text": "is to shake together."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 529260.0,
      "end_time": 532260.0,
      "text": "And the proper translation of &quot;cogito ergo sum&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 532260.0,
      "end_time": 536260.0,
      "text": "is &quot;I shake things up, therefore I am.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 536260.0,
      "end_time": 538260.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 538260.0,
      "end_time": 540260.0,
      "text": "Metaphor shakes things up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 540260.0,
      "end_time": 545260.0,
      "text": "giving us everything from Shakespeare to scientific discovery in the process."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 545260.0,
      "end_time": 548260.0,
      "text": "The mind is a plastic snow dome,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 548260.0,
      "end_time": 550260.0,
      "text": "the most beautiful, most interesting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 550260.0,
      "end_time": 553260.0,
      "text": "and most itself, when, as Elvis put it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 553260.0,
      "end_time": 555260.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s all shook up."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 555260.0,
      "end_time": 557260.0,
      "text": "And metaphor keeps the mind shaking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 557260.0,
      "end_time": 560260.0,
      "text": "rattling and rolling, long after Elvis has left the building."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 560260.0,
      "end_time": 562260.0,
      "text": "Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 562260.0,
      "end_time": 572260.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}